3. Urges parties to utilize UNMIN's expertise to complete outstanding aspects of its mandate by 15 January 2011;

4. Calls on the Government of Nepal and the Unified Communist Party of Nepal (Maoist) to implement the 13 September 2010 agreement and a timetabled action plan for integration and rehabilitation of Maoist army personnel;

5. Urges all parties to expedite the peace process through cooperation and consensus;

6. Requests parties to ensure the safety, security, and freedom of movement of UNMIN personnel;

7. Requests the Secretary-General to report on the implementation of the 13 September agreement by 15 October;

8. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
